  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison sympathizes with Henry Clarke Wright on his mission abroad. Garrison believes that Henry Clarke Wright&apos;s mission will do him good, as well as to &quot;the various great moral and philanthropic enterprises of the age.&quot; Garrison sends his greetings to friends in the British Isles. He mentions the kindnesses he has received from John Murray and William Smeal in Scotland. Garrison&apos;s new baby boy will be named Charles Follen Garrison.</subfield>
